The logical error in this argument is called the fallacy of undistributed middle, where the middle term (in this case, "aircraft") is not distributed in either of the premises but is distributed in the conclusion. To avoid this fallacy, the middle term must be distributed in at least one of the premises when it is distributed in the conclusion.
